100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 14, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing the ongoing turmoil in Turkey following the recent establishment of a republican government. In the United States, a severe winter storm wreaked havoc across the Midwest, disrupting transportation and causing widespread power outages. Meanwhile, the British Parliament debated new measures to support the coal industry amid ongoing labor disputes.
